definition: Belgium/Belgian/abbr. for 比利時|比利时[Bi3 li4 shi2]
to compare/(followed by a noun and adjective) more {adj.} than {noun}/ratio/to gesture/(Taiwan pr. [bi4] in some compounds derived from Classical Chinese)

sentences.english: Californians are no happier than people in Massachusetts.
sentences.chinese: 加州人不比麻省人更快乐。

sentences.english: Is this not of more consequence than a fat red-faced gentleman's sums?
sentences.chinese: 这难道不比那个大胖子红脸先生的帐目更重要？

sentences.english: It hurts them just as much, if not more, than it hurts me.
sentences.chinese: 他们承受的伤害即使不比我多，也和我一样。

sentences.english: Hong Kong isn't as quite as enterprising as Shanghai, and speculative ventures are slow to catch on.
sentences.chinese: 香港城不比上海有作为，新的投机事业发展得极慢。

sentences.english: The quantity of industry-related losses is by no means smaller than direct economic losses.
sentences.chinese: 产业关联性损失的数量丝毫不比直接经济损失来得小。

sentences.english: Nothing more than boxes of iron, too small for standing or lying.
sentences.chinese: 它们不比一个铁箱子大，站直或躺着都嫌太小。

sentences.english: But you far more lovertiful than Zhang Ziyi.
Our prices are not dearer than those in other places.
sentences.chinese: 我们的价格不比剐的地方贵。

sentences.english: This workpiece is no more elastic than that one.
sentences.chinese: 这个工件不比那个工件更有弹性。

sentences.english: We are able to give you an absolute guarantee on quality.
sentences.chinese: 我们可以保证质量不比听装差。

sentences.english: We are not inferior to the Calabrians and we will show that on Sunday.
sentences.chinese: 我们不比南方人差，周末的比赛将证明这一点。

sentences.english: Why don’t men get more oxytocin than women?
sentences.chinese: 为什么男人不比女人获得更多的荷尔蒙？

sentences.english: He will never be able to run and play with you like these other dogs would.
sentences.chinese: 他跑不了，不比其余几只可以陪你玩。

sentences.english: We can avouch for the quality.
sentences.chinese: 我们可以保证质量不比听装差。

sentences.english: This is exactly what is called shocked to compare with.
sentences.chinese: 正所谓不比不知道，一比吓一跳。

sentences.english: Research shows the average person barely does any better than chance.
sentences.chinese: 研究显示，一般人识破谎言的本事不比碰运气强多少。

definition: inferior/not up to par/to fall far short/to be mistaken
fall short by a large amount
not to be inferior in any aspects (idiom)/to surpass/to outdo/(derog.) to be even worse
pinyin: you3 guo4 zhi1 er2 wu2 bu4 ji2

definition: inferior (often in the combination 毫無遜色|毫无逊色, not in the least inferior)
to be on good terms/to be close friends/striving for self-improvement
lit. to have no time for civilities (idiom)/fig. not to be outdone/not to yield to one's opponents
eager to excel/eager to get ahead in life/strong-minded
